<p>The <i><b>Great Soviet Encyclopedia</b></i> (<a href="Russian_language" title="Russian language">Russian</a>: <span lang="ru" xml:lang="ru">Большая советская энциклопедия, or <b>БСЭ</b></span>; <a href="Romanization_of_Russian" title="Romanization of Russian">transliterated</a> <i>Bolshaya sovetskaya entsiklopediya</i>) is one of the largest and most comprehensive Russian <a href="Encyclopedia" title="Encyclopedia">encyclopedias</a> in the world,<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> issued by the <a href="USSR" title="USSR" class="mw-redirect">Soviet state</a> from 1926 to 1990, and again since 2002 (under the name <i>Bolshaya Rossiyskaya entsiklopediya</i> or "<a href="Great_Russian_Encyclopedia" title="Great Russian Encyclopedia">Great Russian Encyclopedia</a>").</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
<tr>
